Text.Value: I do not give you leave to speak. In fact, I suggest you leave Ramazith's Tower immediately. We have no further business.
Roll your eyes.
Witness me - immortal, until the end of all days.
A tide to which I am no longer beholden. Ah, the freedom. You would never understand.
Fitting. I thank you. And now, I give you leave to go.
You have my congratulations.
And a word of advice? Humble yourself. There are powers far greater than you at play. And not all are as merciful as I.
Aha! When last we met, mercenary, I had yet to attain my true form.
You've made a powerful ally today, you know. This tower's capabilities are exceptional, and your enemies are now my own, should I wish them to be.
It is done - it is done! Now - I must fit her into the device before she resurrects. You - take your payment - well earned - and be gone.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slavering hurried excitement; he got what he wanted after the player helped him fight Nightsong.

Text.Value: I suggest you leave before your disrespect is met with an appropriate rebuke.
Leave.
Leave.
You cannot question me. I am as a god. And you are a bit of dross washed in by the tide of fate.
This feels wrong.
What will you do with your immortality, Lorroakan?
Swimming above the tides of fate, I see so much for me to do. So very much indeed.
I give you leave to go - so be gone. And do not call upon Ramazith's Tower again. When I see its services might be of use to you, I will rally of my own accord.
Genius? You paid me to do your work for you.
Witness me - immortal, until the end of all days.
You can count on Ramazith's Tower in future. Something tells me you won't leave Baldur's Gate without a few... fireworks.
I thank you for your role in my ascension. I hope you're enjoying your newfound wealth. It pleases me to reward my faithful.
Whatever I wish. Forever, forever, whatever I wish.
A pleasure doing business with you.
Congratulations, Lorroakan. Eternity suits you.
It does. I was born for power. Made for it. And now, high above the tides of fate, I feel, at last, at home.
Go cry into your sack of gold.
It was no dream I had - it was a plan. Carefully crafted, carefully executed by sheer force of genius.
It's wonderful to see someone achieve their dreams.
Come, boy, don't stand there gawping. We have much work to do.
Of course it was.

EditorData.NodeContext: Impatient, trying to get player ot leave.

Synopsis: Lorroakan's dialoge after winning the fight against Nightsong. In gameplay he will attempt to fit her into the soul cage device (after this dialogue-- this should remain bronze).
